fields.name: Americano
fields.description: What everyone means when they just want a coffee. Allegedly named after American soldiers fighting in Italy, who would dilute an espresso with hot water, the Americano has become the standard coffee in English-speaking countries.

fields.name: Earl Grey Tea
fields.description: A black tea infused with bergamot, Earl Grey is a popular blend named for a 19th century British prime minster.

fields.name: Xocolatl
fields.description: Everybody's guilty pleasure, our signature hot chocolate uses the finest Oaxacan cacao beans from a Fair Trade and Rainforest Council-certified supplier.

fields.name: VLT
fields.description: A new take on a classic sandwich, our VLT switches bacon and mayonnaise for an award-winning grilled tofu and Hellmann's vegan mayonnaise.

fields.name: Seabrook's Crisps
fields.description: One of our baristas swears that these are the best crisps out there, a big claim in the land of Tayto but we're inclined to agree!

fields.name: Yerba Mate Gourd and Bombilla
fields.description: Popular among South American football stars like Lionel Messi and Luis Suarez, yerba mate is the ultimate energy kick. Handmade in Argentina.

fields.name: Machiatto
fields.description: Roughly translated as 'marked' or 'spotted', machiattos add a dash of milk to the traditional espresso.

fields.name: Liz Claiborne Audra Classic Fit Straight Leg Pants
Vegan Fillet Roll
fields.description: A staple of the Irish pallette, we couldn't sell hot food without offering a chicken fillet roll. Of course we wanted to twist the concept, and we scoured Europe to find the best vegan fillet out there.
